\text{Given}\quad y = \sqrt{k\sqrt{k\sqrt{k \sqrt{k}_{\;\ldots\;\infty}}}}\quad \text{ where }\,k\geq 0,\;\;\text{find the value of }\,y.
k
y
y=0
y=k
 y=\sqrt{k\cdot\sqrt{k\cdot\sqrt{\dots}}} 
 \frac{y^2}k=\sqrt{k\cdot\sqrt{\dots}} 
 \frac{y^2}k=y 
y=\sqrt{k\cdot\sqrt{k\cdot\sqrt{\dots}}}=k^{1/2+1/4+1/8+...}=k^{\frac{1}{2}\frac{1}{1-1/2}}=k^1=k
y=\sqrt{k\cdot\sqrt{k\cdot\sqrt{\dots}}} = k^{\frac{1}{2}}k^{\frac{1}{4}}k^{\frac{1}{8}}\cdots = k^{\frac{1}{2}+\frac{1}{4}+\frac{1}{8}+\cdots} = k^1 = k
